         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 6/9/75. ¶  ¶ By the Ship Essex, most esteemed friend, I have forwarded to my London Agents (Mess. Blackith &amp; Co.) Cox's Quay, Lower Thames Street) about 450 Museum plants for you. The coll...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">75.09.06a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Decaisne</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Bibliothèque de l'Institut de France, Paris.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">6/9/75.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>By the Ship Essex, most esteemed friend, I have forwarded to my London Agents (Mess. Blackith &amp; Co.) Cox's Quay, Lower Thames Street) about 450 Museum plants for you. The collection contains many rarities from North East Australia. Should you or the illustrious Brogniart<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. Brongniart.</p>
               </note> recognize among the new plants any, which you may have from the Sunda-Islands or New Caledonia, then I should be grateful to receive your information on them. I am now continuing to arrange the supplemental collections of my Museum, &amp; shall therefore be able to send you further contributions.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The present sending comprises many <name key="Sapindaceae">Sapindaceae</name>, <name key="Rutaceae">Rutaceae</name>, <name key="Proteaceae">Proteaceae</name>, <name key="Gramineae">Gramineae</name> &amp;c.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have simultaneously forwarded the last volume of the Fragmenta.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Distribution of vol. 8 of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Fragmenta</seg> was approved on 14 May 1875 (see notes to M to W. Odgers, 20 April 1875).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With profound regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
